 Four people have died with several others injured in an accident at Sobea area along the Nakuru-Eldoret Highway. ALSO READ:

12 dead in accident along Nairobi-Naivasha highway The Friday dawn accident involved a 14 seater matatu and truck. Salgaa base Commander Richard Sang said the matatu was from Eldoret and headed to Nakuru when it rammed into the truck, also headed to Nakuru. Those injured have been rushed to nearby health facilities. More to follow. Know if news is factual and true. Text 'NEWS' to 22840 and always receive verified news updates.